blog.title: What is life without Kpop?
blog.description: Too many fandoms to name, and most certainly too many biases. I'm basically just trash when it comes to k-pop.

summary: This past weekend was more amazing than I think I ever could have imagined. I got to see BTS, my faves, with my favorite person...
body:
I Still don’t know how to put my feelings into words, but I’m going to try.

This past weekend was more amazing than I think I ever could have imagined. I got to see BTS, my faves, with my favorite person @exo-waithowdidigethere, not just once, but twice. I got to see them in soundcheck. Even thinking about it makes me cry, but I want to put it down somewhere.

These boys work so incredibly hard, and it certainly shows. The energy they put out is better than any show I’ve ever been to. All of them are more handsome than I ever could have imagined photos do them absolutely no justice. Especially Namjoon, Hoseok, and Seokjin. They just have an aura around them that makes them seem like they absolutely glow. And I’m not talking about glowing from their makeup. I saw them in soundcheck with zero makeup and they still glowed. They also seem so much larger in person. Even Jimin seemed large.

The studio versions of their songs do absolutely no justice to their voices. Especially Seokjin. He has the most amazing tone to his voice that is either smoothed over in editing or unable to be picked up in recording. It’s beautiful though. It’s not just him though, after seeing them live, the studio tracks just don’t sound as good for any of them.

It’s so hard for me to put any of this into words even now, as I’m still overwhelmed by it. Hobi and Jimin are such natural performers, always managing to interact with the fans and make them feel special. Hobi was constantly trying to make eye contact with people (I was one of them and nearly died) and constantly waving at people. He would crouch down to try and get closer. Jimin was also waving and making eye contact as he danced.

I made eye contact with Hoseok, Tae and Joonie waved at us, Jin and Joonie both blew kisses in our direction. Jungkook waved at us and smiled his cute Bunny smile. We were blessed by Hobi water. It was all so incredible. I might feel like a hoe now, with Hobi joining Joonie in the ult bias spot, but it was certainly worth it 😂

And as much as I’m suffering now, I can’t wait to see them again in Citi field again. The energy from the fans in Hamilton was so incredible that I can’t even begin to imagine what it might be like with 40,000 of us. I don’t think my husband has any idea what he’s walking in to 😂😂😅. Maybe after that I’ll actually be able to process my feelings and put the entire experience into words.

Now have some pictures of us looking cute for this concert.

summary: “I’d like to ask all of you: What is your name? What excites you, and makes your heart beat? Tell me your story. I wanna hear...
text: I’d like to ask all of you: What is your name? What excites you, and makes your heart beat? Tell me your story. I wanna hear your voice. I wanna hear your conviction. No matter who you are, where you’re from, your skin color, your gender identity: just speak yourself. Find your name, and find your voice, by speaking yourself.

In times of loneliness

Your music saved me

Your words touched my heart

And I will never forget

How grateful I am

That you came into my life,

Bangtan Sonyeondan.

summary: There are only two kind of Titanic Movies in the World:
title: There are only two kind of Titanic Movies in the World:
body:
One, starring Kate Winslet and Leonardo DiCaprio. Truly a tragic and moving story… of young love and several other lives that suffered…

The other starring BTS Kim SeokJin and Park Jimin. A beautiful reenact comedy movie revolving around young love who had no trust in each other… and rest of the BTS that suffered at this comedic parody…

Coincidentally speaking, the second type is my favorite 😂😂
